# Per-repo .gitignore — layers on top of ~/.config/git/ignore (the global).
# The global already covers: secrets (.env*, *.pem, *.key, *credentials*, *secret*),
# OS noise, editor dirs, node_modules, dist/build, Python caches, deploy state, logs.
# Only add what's SPECIFIC to this assignment below.

# -------- Assignment inputs / sensitive material --------
# Keep the brief and any provided sample/clinical data out of git by default.
# Un-ignore specific safe files with `!path` if you decide they should be tracked.
/assignment/
/brief/
/data/
/samples/
*.local.md

